1
00:00:03,720 --> 00:00:06,680
Why do you think they can't manage without me?
-I don't think so, honey. I'm sure.

2
00:00:06,760 --> 00:00:08,880
I’m gone for one day,
and everything falls apart.

3
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:11,040
Calm down, not everything falls apart that quickly.

4
00:00:11,120 --> 00:00:13,560
Honey, some people are irreplaceable. Period.

5
00:00:14,120 --> 00:00:16,600
Cemeteries are full of people
who thought they were irreplaceable.

6
00:00:16,680 --> 00:00:18,720
It's obvious you're your mother's son.

7
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:21,600
It's amazing. Every conversation with you
ends up at a cemetery.

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:24,680
Sit down, sit down, can you take
the turns a bit slower?

9
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:28,000
I don't have gyro, and with every turn I feel
the sauce reaching the edge of the pot,

10
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:30,840
and in a second I'm getting a shower of cumin.
-It's not cumin.

11
00:00:31,480 --> 00:00:33,440
So what's in the meatballs with cumin?
-Turmeric.

12
00:00:34,520 --> 00:00:36,320
But...
-Okay, honey, I know what I'm doing.

13
00:00:36,400 --> 00:00:37,280
Watch out, bump.

14
00:00:41,120 --> 00:00:43,720
Look at me, look at me and...

15
00:00:53,680 --> 00:00:56,760
Okay, I'm going to set the table.
-No, no. No. Uh...

16
00:00:57,160 --> 00:00:59,360
Help me get up. I want
to set the table with you.

17
00:00:59,440 --> 00:01:02,360
No, no. I can manage on my own. Come on.

18
00:01:02,440 --> 00:01:05,000
The doctor told you not to step
on your foot for a week, so what...

19
00:01:05,160 --> 00:01:08,640
No need to insist.
-What, but I'm not going to help you set the table?

20
00:01:10,320 --> 00:01:14,200
Helping you... no need to make a drama out of it.

21
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:16,280
Table.
-What drama?

22
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:20,680
I'm setting the table with you,
I'm clearing the table with you

23
00:01:21,480 --> 00:01:25,040
together for so many weeks.
-Okay, so one time not,

24
00:01:25,240 --> 00:01:27,600
so one time I'll do it alone.
Next week you'll be healthy

25
00:01:28,040 --> 00:01:30,400
and then we can do it together again, like always.

26
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:32,600
I'm sure he won't get mad.

27
00:01:32,880 --> 00:01:34,360
Who?
-The table.

28
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:41,400
Okay, but I don't agree to let you set
this table alone, with your back.

29
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:43,360
Wait for the kids' backs.
-Okay.

30
00:01:43,480 --> 00:01:46,080
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

31
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:49,720
Shabbat Shalom.
-Mom, what's up? How are you?

32
00:01:50,200 --> 00:01:52,720
We need to help Dad set the table.
-Sure, sure, Shai...

33
00:01:52,920 --> 00:01:55,120
I'm going to the kitchen.
-Sure, I'll help with the table.

34
00:01:55,200 --> 00:01:57,640
Thanks, Shai, thanks.
-How's your foot feeling?

35
00:01:57,720 --> 00:02:00,640
It's fine. Nonsense, it'll pass eventually.
-Yeah? Are you eating a lot of cheese?

36
00:02:01,240 --> 00:02:03,040
What cheese?
-No, because at this age

37
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,000
all the calcium starts to slip away.

38
00:02:04,880 --> 00:02:07,560
What age are you talking about
when you say "at this age"?

39
00:02:07,640 --> 00:02:11,240
Thanks.
-I... I mean around the age of...

40
00:02:11,680 --> 00:02:14,160
Exactly the age of... much younger too.

41
00:02:14,680 --> 00:02:18,840
That's nonsense, right? A hernia in the foot.
It has nothing to do with calcium loss.

42
00:02:19,480 --> 00:02:21,480
Shai said there's a friend
who knows about these things.

43
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,600
Yeah, he knows about feet.
-What, is he an orthopedist?

44
00:02:24,680 --> 00:02:27,880
No, no, he's kind of...
-A rheumatologist?

45
00:02:28,680 --> 00:02:30,360
What did this rheumatologist say? Is he coming?

46
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,800
Okay, rheumatologist.

47
00:02:33,240 --> 00:02:37,560
The rheumatologist said he’d drop by later
to see what's wrong with you.

48
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:41,120
It's really nice to have someone at home who can drop by.
-Great, Sali.

49
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:44,920
Funny. Thanks, Shai, thanks.

50
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:47,720
I really don't trust that girl who took care of me.

51
00:02:48,720 --> 00:02:52,840
Okay. Come on, I'll show you how to set the table.

52
00:02:52,920 --> 00:02:54,920
Silvan, I've already set
a few tables in my life.

53
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,640
Not this one, not this one. This one has a specific order

54
00:02:58,720 --> 00:03:02,760
that's very, very special and needs to be done
exactly in order. If not, it won't open.

55
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,440
You know what? It could even break.

56
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,000
Okay?
-What's the order?

57
00:03:06,080 --> 00:03:09,280
Please. Put your hand there, right in front of you.

58
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:11,680
Yeah, navigate
come
and touch this

59
00:03:11,760 --> 00:03:13,680
Okay, take the little piece, pull it to the left,

60
00:03:14,160 --> 00:03:17,920
now lift it up and to the right.

61
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:20,200
Okay? Now pull, pull the... this.

62
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,440
It's not coming out.
-Please.

63
00:03:22,520 --> 00:03:23,920
No, Sali, he's on my side.

64
00:03:24,440 --> 00:03:29,880
You need to go right
then up, then left, and it’ll come out.

65
00:03:30,440 --> 00:03:31,680
And Shai
Kai.

66
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,120
Go to the right now. Same thing.

67
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:38,600
Same clip, go up and turn right.

68
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:40,480
Pull them and...

69
00:03:42,280 --> 00:03:44,520
For the first time,
I think it looks really nice.

70
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,480
Hello sis, Shabbat Shalom.
-What's up, sis?

71
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:53,480
About what?
-About his tasks.

72
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:57,160
Are you talking about the lettuce salad?
-Yeah, that’s what they gave you to make, right?

73
00:03:57,720 --> 00:04:00,080
You caught me just as I was going to wash my hands.

74
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:02,400
I've been with this lettuce dryer for two hours,

75
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:05,160
I can't get it open,
and I’m stuck with lettuce inside.

76
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:08,520
We asked you to make a lettuce salad,
and you got stuck with that too?

77
00:04:09,200 --> 00:04:12,240
I didn't get stuck with the lettuce,
I got stuck with the dryer.

78
00:04:12,360 --> 00:04:13,360
Why complicate everything?

79
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:18,959
Have you seen Shai?
-Great.

80
00:04:19,519 --> 00:04:20,560
What happened, Rachel?

81
00:04:22,400 --> 00:04:25,200
No, it’s nothing, just my leg. Come on.

82
00:04:25,760 --> 00:04:29,040
Sorry, excuse me, sorry.
I'm just worried they won't manage

83
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:32,600
to get everything done in the kitchen on time.
-No, don’t worry, don’t worry at all.

84
00:04:32,680 --> 00:04:34,200
Someone's taking care of it. Trust me.

85
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:39,520
They’re already on Wednesday, they’re already busy
and washing whoever is whatever. You get it?

86
00:04:39,600 --> 00:04:42,360
Everything will be ready on time and in place.

87
00:04:42,920 --> 00:04:44,640
Right?
-True. Rachel, sit back and enjoy.

88
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:49,920
All day she’s cooking, she’s cleaning,
she’s doing this...

89
00:04:50,000 --> 00:04:53,880
So what’s the surprise she fell from her leg?
-Funny.

90
00:04:54,880 --> 00:04:57,840
Well, I can't just sit here,
I want to see what's happening in the kitchen.

91
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:01,160
Shai, take me to the kitchen, please.
I’ll just sit. I’ll just sit.

92
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,120
I promise.

93
00:05:02,200 --> 00:05:03,680
I’ll help you.
-You promise not to touch anything?

94
00:05:03,760 --> 00:05:05,160
No, I won’t touch, won’t touch.

95
00:05:06,920 --> 00:05:07,880
Careful, careful.

96
00:05:14,840 --> 00:05:18,040
Is there a chance you could switch with me?
-No, sweetie. I’ve already finished my tasks.

97
00:05:18,120 --> 00:05:19,960
-What did you make?

98
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:23,200
The green beans and the meatballs.
-Let me taste.

99
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,520
Can I too?
-What are you doing here?

100
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:27,200
Shai, why are you bringing her here?
-She wanted to see how it’s going,

101
00:05:27,280 --> 00:05:29,640
she promised not to do anything.
-She can’t not do anything,

102
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:32,280
I know her.
-Come on, sit, sweetie. Relax. Here,

103
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:36,120
I’m just sitting and watching. That’s all.
Mom, I’m not doing well with this lettuce salad.

104
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:39,640
Yeah, she has lettuce with claustrophobia.
-It’s allowed, there’s the little thing,

105
00:05:39,720 --> 00:05:42,240
move it to the right.
-Oh.

106
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:49,560
You see?
-Okay, I’ll take the lettuce.

107
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:52,880
No, no, no. No way.
-What’s wrong? I’ll make a lettuce salad sitting down.

108
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:56,240
No. Shai, get her out of here now.
-Rachel, you promised not to do anything. Come on...

109
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:59,760
Okay, enough, but look at the lettuce.
-It’ll be fine.

110
00:06:00,280 --> 00:06:02,240
Wash it.
-Get her out!

111
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:08,440
And put oil, lemon, and salt, so it has some flavor.

112
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:09,680
Now listen to me carefully:

113
00:06:10,840 --> 00:06:15,640
You’re immediately making the lettuce salad.
-Okay.

114
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:19,160
I wanted to check the clock, see
how long it’ll take until they bring you back,

115
00:06:19,400 --> 00:06:22,080
I didn’t get to check the clock...
-Come on, Rachel, sit here,

116
00:06:22,760 --> 00:06:25,280
and don’t worry. Okay?
Everything, everything will be fine in the kitchen.

117
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:28,880
Okay? Did you see what a mess there was with the lettuce?

118
00:06:29,440 --> 00:06:31,360
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

119
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:35,360
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

120
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,840
Shabbat Shalom, Shabbat Shalom, my sweethearts.

121
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:38,840
So what, Mom, a week off?

122
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:42,240
Forget it, I don’t want a break, I want to be healthy.

123
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:43,280
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

124
00:06:43,360 --> 00:06:46,200
Come on, it’s just a leg.
You won’t believe what Alin did.

125
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:50,080
I made mdurasa in the special pot you bought me.
-Mdurasa?

126
00:06:50,640 --> 00:06:53,160
Yeah, I’m going to put it in the kitchen.
-How did it turn out?

127
00:06:53,240 --> 00:06:56,360
Mdurasa is the red stuff, right?

128
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:02,640
As much as it looks like a cast, behind it
are many weeks of kitchen wisdom.

129
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:04,400
You won’t believe how delicious it turned out.

130
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:07,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

131
00:07:07,240 --> 00:07:09,160
Shabbat Shalom.
-Shabbat Shalom.

132
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:13,480
Mom, you won’t believe what I made,
mdurasa in the special pot you bought me.

133
00:07:13,640 --> 00:07:16,520
I’m putting it in the kitchen.
-You won’t believe how tasty it turned out.

134
00:07:17,960 --> 00:07:20,200
Shai, take me to the kitchen.

135
00:07:20,920 --> 00:07:25,720
I need to see how Alin and Orna
are mdurasa-ing each other.

136
00:07:26,240 --> 00:07:27,280
Slow, slow, slow.

137
00:07:33,760 --> 00:07:35,120
Here, Mom.

138
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,320
This is funny.
-What a scene. Okay, come on, let’s go.

139
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,960
Can we officially declare

140
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,520
International Mdurasa Day?
-Yes.

141
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:43,080
Totally.
-We achieved our goal,

142
00:07:43,160 --> 00:07:46,400
Mdurasa for every worker.
-Ugh, it still doesn’t taste good to me.

143
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:48,040
What?
-The poor lettuce?

144
00:07:48,120 --> 00:07:48,960
What’s the problem?

145
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:52,440
Add a bit of vinegar, a bit of olive oil.

146
00:07:54,440 --> 00:07:57,480
It tastes like grass with fertilizer.
-Is everything okay here?

147
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:59,840
Honey, why did you send her back?
-She insisted because of the mdurasas.

148
00:08:00,520 --> 00:08:03,720
What, did you both happen to make mdurasa?

149
00:08:03,800 --> 00:08:05,760
Yeah. In the pot you bought me.
-Yeah, in the pot you bought me.

150
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,680
Her too.
-Her too.

151
00:08:06,760 --> 00:08:08,360
Come on, it’s fine, Mom. Nothing happened.

152
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:13,600
How nice. Can I taste?
-No. Shai!

153
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:18,040
I bet you that Orna’s mdurasa
beats the Russian version hands down.

154
00:08:19,400 --> 00:08:23,080
It’s easy to check. Want us to ask
everyone whose mdurasa is the tastiest?

155
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:25,400
I love competitions like this.

156
00:08:26,560 --> 00:08:30,080
Orna’s is more attractive, that’s clear.
I’m saying this loud and clear.

157
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:34,320
Yeah? Then I hereby declare
the “Mdurasa Showdown.”

158
00:08:34,799 --> 00:08:37,600
You’re going to have a problem. You know
what the problem is? The pots are identical.

159
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:42,320
Maybe you should mark them because you won’t know
which mdurasa belongs to which pot?

160
00:08:42,400 --> 00:08:44,320
No, no, no. I don’t need to mark anything.

161
00:08:44,400 --> 00:08:46,520
I can spot our mdurasa from 100 meters away.

162
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,600
What, it’s not obvious that Orna cooks better?
-Not at all.

163
00:08:49,680 --> 00:08:50,800
Look at her! Look at her.

164
00:08:51,640 --> 00:08:54,160
It’s because I switch ingredients
faster. That’s all.

165
00:08:55,560 --> 00:08:58,920
What ingredients is he talking about, Dad?
-Come on, the essential nutrients, how do you say that?

166
00:08:59,560 --> 00:09:01,920
Metabolism, metabolism.

167
00:09:02,680 --> 00:09:05,360
Yeah, metabolism.
So mine is faster.

168
00:09:06,720 --> 00:09:09,720
Rachel, come on, we’re going back.
-When is the foot doctor coming?

169
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:14,480
Doctor? Does a doctor need to come?

170
00:09:14,720 --> 00:09:16,880
He’s a foot specialist, because...

171
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,840
Doctor! Move out of the way.

172
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:24,520
Come on, have you tasted the mdurasa?
-Which one did I taste?

173
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:27,680
They wouldn’t let me near the pots. They formed a human shield.

174
00:09:27,880 --> 00:09:30,160
Better this way. It’ll keep the tension until the mdurasa finale.

175
00:09:30,600 --> 00:09:31,760
What finale?

176
00:09:32,400 --> 00:09:35,200
They’re having a competition for which mdurasa is better.

177
00:09:35,920 --> 00:09:38,640
Tell me, what do you think about Mom’s voice
counting as three votes?

178
00:09:39,000 --> 00:09:43,440
No problem, Orna is her daughter.
-Good luck to you all. Break a leg.

179
00:09:44,280 --> 00:09:45,920
It’s just a crack!

180
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:50,600
Wait, if you made mdurasa
and you made mdurasa too,

181
00:09:51,640 --> 00:09:53,600
So, Mom says no one made rice?

182
00:09:53,680 --> 00:09:56,000
We don’t need rice, there’s plenty of food.
-What a mess.

183
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,520
Of course it’s a mess. You think?
No Friday without rice.

184
00:09:58,600 --> 00:10:00,160
I know your mom too, she’ll sneak and buy some.

185
00:10:00,240 --> 00:10:02,160
Alright, let’s get the rice going.

186
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:05,680
Alin, rice isn’t a quick fix.

187
00:10:05,760 --> 00:10:08,840
Alin, you make rice with love.

188
00:10:08,920 --> 00:10:09,920
Just like you make mashed potatoes.

189
00:10:10,240 --> 00:10:11,880
Mashed potatoes? Mom will kill you.
-For sure.

190
00:10:11,960 --> 00:10:14,640
Okay, listen up.
First, you fry the onion.

191
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:18,440
What’s frying onions got to do with rice?
Not every dish starts with frying.

192
00:10:19,000 --> 00:10:21,720
You can boil water, add some rice,
a bit of salt, fresh.

193
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:25,160
Is that a recipe from the book "Everything's Bland and Olive Oil"?

194
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:29,320
No, it’s from "Fry, Spice, and Get Grossed Out."
Heartburn on the house.

195
00:10:29,400 --> 00:10:33,000
No way I’m washing rice here
like in a hospital.

196
00:10:33,080 --> 00:10:35,560
Or like at Shai’s mom’s place.

197
00:10:36,560 --> 00:10:39,960
So what? When’s your doctor friend coming?

198
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,160
He’s at a soccer game.

199
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:45,440
He said he’d come when the game’s over,
so don’t expect a doctor in a white coat.

200
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,040
He’s actually a paramedic.

201
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:51,400
But here’s the thing, he’s a massage therapist for soccer teams.

202
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:55,560
From the national league, from League A,
so he’s a real foot expert.

203
00:10:56,160 --> 00:10:58,760
Who got cold feet and isn’t coming.

204
00:10:59,360 --> 00:11:03,480
I don’t get it. What is he? A paramedic?
A doctor? A medic?

205
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:06,200
Is he a nurse?
-What? No way, he’s a medic,

206
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:09,040
a senior medic. That’s half the studies.

207
00:11:10,040 --> 00:11:13,880
Got it. It’s medical studies on one leg, basically.

208
00:11:14,640 --> 00:11:17,600
Just so you know, those masseurs
you see on the fields are like magicians.

209
00:11:17,920 --> 00:11:21,840
Yeah, except instead of a wand, they have a spray.
-Well, honestly, he’s seen a lot of feet

210
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:24,800
in his life.
-Tell me, his Achilles heel... heels?

211
00:11:26,520 --> 00:11:28,560
What’s up?
-No, I just had to get out of the kitchen.

212
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:31,360
What’s going on? Alin’s taking over everything.
Thinks she’s Stalin.

213
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,360
That’s the lettuce.
-No, no. That’s the rice.

214
00:11:33,440 --> 00:11:35,080
I’m not responsible for what happens to that rice.

215
00:11:35,400 --> 00:11:36,840
Everything’s fine in the kitchen, Mom.

216
00:11:38,320 --> 00:11:40,200
Shai, take me to the kitchen.

217
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:42,600
But Rachel...
-Take me there!

218
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:47,040
Oh, he’s here.
-Blessed is the healer of the sick, blessed is the healer of the sick.

219
00:11:47,920 --> 00:11:48,760
Hello.

220
